{"title":"OneUp Components New Hubs Retail for $369.97 a Hubset!","link":"https://theradavist.com/oneup-components-hubs/","date":1719327609000,"content":"<p><em><a href=\"https://www.oneupcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">OneUp</a>, the makers of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/oneup-v3-dropper-post-review/\" target=\"_blank\">one of the best dropper posts</a> – <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/oneup-components-edc-tool-system-fits-in-a-pump/\" target=\"_blank\">and a whole lot more</a> – just announced all new hubs. Lightweight, fully sealed, durable hubs with high-quality bearings, available in 7 anodized colors. Let’s check them out.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"861\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Exploded-View.jpg?fit=1200,861&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Exploded-View.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Exploded-View.jpg?resize=1200,517&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Exploded-View.jpg?resize=768,331&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Exploded-View.jpg?resize=1536,661&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>These new hubs rely on a 44T ratchet system and feature a fully-machined, super light 7075 aluminum body. This simple design has fewer parts and is lightweight.</p>\n<p><strong>OneUp Hubs Quick Hits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Spacing: Boost front and rear</li>\n<li>Holes: 28 and 32</li>\n<li>Engagement: 44 points, 8.2 degrees Weight front: 142g</li>\n<li>Weight rear: 220g (with XDr freehub)</li>\n<li>Colors: Black, red, green, blue, orange, purple and grey</li>\n<li>Material: 7075 T6 Aluminum</li>\n<li>Freehub options: XDr, Microspline, and HG (all with tool-free installation) Spokes: J-Bend only</li>\n<li>Brake Mount: IS 6 Bolt only</li>\n<li>End Caps: Double sealed (tool-free installation)</li>\n<li>Bearings: Enduro Abec 5 (Front – MR17287, Rear 6902, Freehub 6802) Freehub Seal: Enduro</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Price:</strong></p>\n<p>Hubset $369.97 USD / $ 499.97 CAD / € 369.97 / £ 314.97<br />\nFront Hub $99.99 USD / $134.99 CAD / €99.99 / £84.99<br />\nRear Hub $219.99 USD / $296.99 CAD / €219.99 / £185.99<br />\nFreehubs: $49.99 USD / $67.99 CAD / €49.99 / £43.99</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-HG-Microspline-XDr-Freehubs.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-HG-Microspline-XDr-Freehubs.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-HG-Microspline-XDr-Freehubs.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-HG-Microspline-XDr-Freehubs.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-HG-Microspline-XDr-Freehubs.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Purple-Exploded-44T-Ratchet.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Purple-Exploded-44T-Ratchet.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Purple-Exploded-44T-Ratchet.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Purple-Exploded-44T-Ratchet.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Rear-Hub-Purple-Exploded-44T-Ratchet.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The hubs utilize J-bend spokes only and have an optimized flange spacing, designed to improve the strength and stiffness of wheels built using the OneUp hubs.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div><span>﻿</span><span><span></span></span><span></span></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p>OneUP is all about making it easier for shops: the wheel build specs (PCD, Flange Distance) are laser etched on the hub body and the freehubs are all available individually.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1354\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Front-Hub-On-Bike.jpg?fit=1200,1354&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Front-Hub-On-Bike.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Front-Hub-On-Bike.jpg?resize=1200,812&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Front-Hub-On-Bike.jpg?resize=768,520&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Front-Hub-On-Bike.jpg?resize=1536,1040&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>OneUp Hubs use premium Enduro™ ABEC 5 cartridge bearings in standard sizes that are readily available in local bike shops around the world. They’re spaced as wide as possible to reduce wear, reduce sideloading and increase bearing life. And when they do eventually wear out, the design of the hub shell makes it easy to replace bearings yourself.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Hub-Colour-Range.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Hub-Colour-Range.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Hub-Colour-Range.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Hub-Colour-Range.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/OneUp-Components-Hub-Colour-Range.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Available in 7 anodized colors to match your bike.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1600\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Hub_ComparisonTable.jpg?fit=1200,388&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Hub_ComparisonTable.jpg?w=1600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Hub_ComparisonTable.jpg?resize=1200,291&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Hub_ComparisonTable.jpg?resize=768,186&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Hub_ComparisonTable.jpg?resize=1536,372&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://www.oneupcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">OneUp</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/oneup-components-hubs/\">OneUp Components New Hubs Retail for $369.97 a Hubset!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"6dd0bb3583fe0be0d1847c76c9ae56ab3fe6c6d20faf19485526eba111fe9cb6","category":"Cycling"}